Something less than £40, if the text is correct.

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
Thayer's Note: A reminder that this equivalent dates to 1924; in 2003, the figure would be a bit less than $200 or £130.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note24" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref24
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">24</A>
179 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note25" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref25
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">25</A>
What Velleius probably had in mind was the <SPAN CLASS="whole">aedile</SPAN>&shy;ship in 213 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> of Publius and Marcus Scipio, referred to by
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Polybius/10*.html#4
	"TARGET="Polybius_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Polybius,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Polybius x.4</A>. Hence some editors have supposed that <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">aedilibus</SPAN> or <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">in aedilitate</SPAN> have dropped out of the text; but this is hardly necessary. The author is thinking simply of brothers who were colleagues in office.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note26" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref26
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">26</A>
108 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note27" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref27
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">27</A>
He is referring to the Jugurthine War.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note28" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref28
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">28</A>
The <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Fabulae Atellanae</SPAN> or <I>Atellan Farce.</I> While not the inventor he may have been the first to give these farces literary form.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note29" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref29
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">29</A>
Censors in 125 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note30" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref30
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">30</A>
A little more than £50.

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
Thayer's Note: in 2003, a little more than $2500 or £1600.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note31" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref31
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">31</A>
122 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note32" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref32
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">32</A>
109‑8 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note33" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref33
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">33</A>
107 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note34" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref34
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">34</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Praecaventibus fatis</SPAN> is variously interpreted. Krause takes it to mean that the fates were seeking to guard against the future rivalry and discord of these two men; Kritz, wrongly, I think, that the fates were warning Marius in advance that Sulla was destined to be his successful opponent.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note35" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref35
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">35</A>
104 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note36" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref36
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">36</A>
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#8.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Bk. ii. ch. 8</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note37" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref37
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">37</A>
105 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note38" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref38
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">38</A>
113 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note39" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref39
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">39</A>
109 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note40" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref40
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">40</A>
104 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note41" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref41
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">41</A>
102 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note42" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref42
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">42</A>
101 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note43" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref43
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">43</A>
100 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note44" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref44
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">44</A>
Saturninus was elected tribune for the third time; Glaucia was praetor and desired the <SPAN CLASS="whole">consul</SPAN>&shy;ship.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note45" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref45
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">45</A>
91 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note46" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref46
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">46</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#6.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
ch. vi</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note47" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref47
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">47</A>
91 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note48" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref48
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">48</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Pius</SPAN> here means "dutiful towards his father."


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note49" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref49
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">49</A>
The number was increased from four to six in 198 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> It was increased to eight by Sulla.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note50" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref50
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">50</A>
The <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">sagum</SPAN> or military cloak symbolized war as the <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">toga</SPAN> symbolized peace.

	<DIV CLASS="mynote">
Thayer's Note: For details, see the article
	<A CLASS="smallcaps" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/secondary/SMIGRA*/Sagum.html
	"TARGET="princeps"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,1,WIDTH,165)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Sagum
	</A>
in Smith's <I>Dictionary of Greek and Roman Antiquities</I>.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note51" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref51
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">51</A>
<I>i.e.</I> before the war began. What Velleius had in mind in using <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">maluerunt</SPAN> is a little vague. The original "choice" lay between granting the <SPAN CLASS="whole">citizen</SPAN>&shy;ship and war. They chose the latter alternative. After the war was over they granted to their enemies in defeat the <SPAN CLASS="whole">citizen</SPAN>&shy;ship


<A ID="p83x"></A><SPAN CLASS="pagenum">(p83)</SPAN>which they might have conferred in the beginning and so avoided the war.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note52" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref52
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">52</A>
88 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note53" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref53
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">53</A>
88 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN><!-- identical with previous note and next -->


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note54" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref54
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">54</A>
88 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN><!-- identical with two previous notes -->


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note55" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref55
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">55</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Duumvir</SPAN> was the title of the chief official in the Roman colonies. Like the consuls in Rome there were two of them.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note56" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref56
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">56</A>
87 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note57" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref57
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">57</A>
The normal strength of a legion was from 5000 to 6000 men. Each legion was divided into ten cohorts.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note58" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref58
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">58</A>
That is, his property was divided among those responsible for his death.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note59" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref59
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">59</A>
For this period and its proscriptions see
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Sulla*.html
	"TARGET="Plutarch_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Plutarch,WIDTH,PlutarchWidth)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Plutarch, <I>Life of Sulla</I></A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note60" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref60
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">60</A>
86 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note61" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref61
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">61</A>
87‑86 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note62" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref62
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">62</A>
<I>i.e.</I> with their Roman besiegers.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note63" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref63
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">63</A>
The province of Asia, <I>i.e.</I> <I>Asia Minor.</I>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note64" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref64
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">64</A>
83 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note65" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref65
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">65</A>
83 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN><!-- identical with previous note -->


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note66" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref66
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">66</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#30
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Chap. XXX</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note67" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref67
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">67</A>
The "fortunate."


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note68" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2A*.html#ref68
